est-xi-how-the-panel-voted |publisher=World Soccer |author=Jamie Rainbow |date=2 July 2013}}</ref>\n* Greatest Football Players of All-Time: No. 1 by ''[[FourFourTwo]]'' magazine, 2017<ref name=\"Murray\"/>\n* Greatest Football Players in World Cup History: No. 1, by ''FourFourTwo'' magazine, 2018<ref>[https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/ranked-25-best-world-cup-players-ever?page=0%2C2 \u201cRanked! The 25 best World Cup players EVER\u201d]. Four Four Two. Retrieved 28 July 2018</ref>\n* [[S.S.C. Napoli#Statistics and records|Napoli all-time Top Scorer]] (1991\u20132017)<ref name=\"Fifa profile\"/><ref name=\"Hamsik\"/>\n* [[Italian Football Hall of Fame]]: 2014<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vivoazzurro.it/en/news/italian-football-hall-of-fame-to-induct-ten-new-stars/ |title=Italian football Hall of Fame to induct ten new stars |date=25 October 2016 |accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Argentine Football Association|AFA Team of All Time]]: 2015<ref>{{cite web |title=La Selecci\u00f3n de Todos los Tiempos |trans-title=The Team of All Time |publisher=Argentine Football Association |language=Spanish |date=4 January 2016 |url=http://www.afa.com.ar/3023/la-seleccion-de-todos-los-tiempos |accessdate=29 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814210638/http://www.afa.com.ar/3023/la-seleccion-de-todos-los-tiempos |archive-date=14 August 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[L'\u00c9quipe]]'s top 50 South-American footballers in history: #2<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Top/Football/top50-joueurs-sud-americains/3/ |title=Top 50 des joueurs sud-am\u00e9ricains de l'histoire |trans-title=Top 50 South-American footballers in history |newspaper=L'\u00c9quipe |language=French |date=4 July 2015 |accessdate=6 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704215531/http://www.lequipe.fr/Top/Football/top50-joueurs-sud-americains/3 |archive-date=4 July 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[International Federation of Football History & Statistics]] (IFFHS) Legends<ref>{{cite web |url=http://iffhs.de/iffhs-has-announced-the-48-football-legend-players/ |title=IFFHS announce the 48 football legend players |publisher=IFFHS |date=25 January 2016 |accessdate=14 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Association football|Argentina}}\n*[[New Maradona]]\n*[[List of association football families]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist}}\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Diego Armando Maradona, ''Yo Soy el Diego'', Planeta Pub. Corp, 2000, {{ISBN|84-08036-74-2}} (I am the Diego). {{in lang|es}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline|Diego Maradona}}\n* [https://www.diegomaradonagroup.com/ Official website]\n* {{Britannica|686139}}\n* {{worldcat id|lccn-n90-719108}}\n\n{{Gimnasia y Esgrima La Plata squad}}\n{{Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n managers}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Argentina squads\n|bg = #6AB5FF\n|fg = white\n|bordercolor = black\n|list1=\n{{Argentina squad 1979 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 1982 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 1986 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 1987 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 1989 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 1990 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 1994 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Awards\n|bg= gold\n|fg= navy\n|list1=\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{s-bef|before={{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Steve Cram]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United Press International Athlete of the Year Award#Male winners|United Press International<br />Athlete of the Year]]|years=1986}}\n{{s-aft|after={{flagicon|CAN}} [[Ben Johnson (Canadian sprinter)|Ben Johnson]]}}\n{{s-bef|before={{flagicon|ARG}} [[Hugo Porta]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=''[[Olimpia Award|Olimpia de Oro]]''|years=1986}}\n{{s-aft|after={{flagicon|ARG}} [[Gabriela Sabatini]]}}\n{{s-bef|before={{flagicon|URS}} [[Sergey Bubka]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[L'\u00c9quipe Champion of Champions]]|years=1986}}\n{{s-aft|after=<del>''{{flagicon|CAN}} [[