colspan=\"8\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Mike Shay\n| colspan=\"5\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"2\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Tina McDowelle\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Laura-Leigh]]\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"7\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Frank Herlihy\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"7\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Kristina Kelly\n| colspan=\"1\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Vail Bloom]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Faith Stowers\n| colspan=\"3\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| {{n/a|}}\n| {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"2\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Raquel Leviss\n| colspan=\"4\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Billie Lee\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cRecurring}}\n| {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Charli Burnett\n| colspan=\"7\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Danica Dow\n| colspan=\"7\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Lisa Vanderpump]]: A successful restaurateur, the co-owner of SUR. Best known as a former cast member of ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]''.\n* [[Scheana Shay]]: A server at SUR, a singer and aspiring actress.\n* [[Stassi Schroeder]] (Seasons 1-Present, Recurring Season 4): A former server at SUR. \n* [[Jax Taylor]]: A bartender at SUR.\n* Tom Sandoval: A former bartender at SUR, now Lisa's business partner at TomTom.\n* [[Kristen Doute]]: A former server at SUR, now a clothing designer\n* Katie Maloney-Schwartz: A former server at SUR, married to Tom Schwartz.\n* Tom Schwartz: (Season 3-Present, Recurring Seasons 1-2) Katie's husband, now Lisa's business partner at TomTom.\n*[[Ariana Madix]]: (Season 3-Present, Recurring Season 2) A former bartender at SUR, in a relationship with Tom Sandoval.\n* James Kennedy: (Season 4-Present, Recurring Season 3) A former busboy at SUR, now a DJ.\n* Lala Kent: (Season 6-Present, Recurring Seasons 4-5) A former hostess at SUR, now engaged to Hollywood producer [[Randall Emmett]].\n* Brittany Cartwright: (Season 6-Present, Recurring Season 5) Jax's wife, a former server at SUR.\n* Beau Clark: (Season 8-present, Recurring Season 7) Stassi's fianc\u00e9.\n* Dayna Kathan: (Season 8-present) A hostess and server at TomTom and SUR.\n* Max Boyens: (Season 8-present) The general manager at TomTom.\n* Brett Caprioni: (Season 8-present) A server at SUR.\n\n===Recurring cast===\n* Ken Todd: Lisa Vanderpump's husband, the co-owner of SUR and successful restaurateur\n*Peter Madrigal: The manager of SUR.\n* Mike Shay: (Season 1-5) Scheana's ex-husband.\n*Tina McDowelle: (Season 1-3) A former server at SUR, a singer.\n*Frank Herlihy: (Season 1) A former bartender at SUR\n*[[Laura-Leigh]]: (Season 1) A former server at SUR, an actress known for [[The Ward (film)|''The Ward'']] and [[The Client List (TV series)|''The Client List'']].\n* Kristina Kelly: (Season 2-7) Stassi's friend, a server at SUR.\n*[[Vail Bloom]]: (Season 3) A former hostess at SUR, an [[Daytime Emmy Award|Emmy]]-nominated actress known for ''[[The Young and the Restless]]''.\n* Faith Stowers: (Seasons 4, 6) A former server at SUR. \n* Raquel Leviss: (Season 5-present) James's girlfriend, a server at SUR.<ref>http://www.bravotv.com/vanderpump-rules/season-5/blogs/5-things-you-need-to-know-about-james-kennedys-girlfriend-raquel</ref>\n* Billie Lee: (Season 6-7) A former hostess at SUR.\n* Charli Burnett: (Season 8-present) A server at SUR.\n* Danica Dow: (Season 8-present) An assistant manager at SUR.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Vanderpump Rules episodes}}\n{{:List of Vanderpump Rules episodes}}\n\n===After Show (2015-16)===\nOn November 6, 2015, Bravo premiered a [[talk show]] titled ''[[Vanderpump Rules After Show]]'' which features conversations between the cast members of ''Vanderpump Rules'' discussing the same week's events and answering questions about their lives both on and off the show. The talk show was hosted by [[Julie Goldman]] and Brandy Howard.\n\n===How They Got Here (2017)===\nOn November 27, 2017 Bravo premiered ''[[Vanderpump Rules: How They Got Here]]'', a recap of all five previous seasons of ''Vanderpump Rules'' before starting the sixth season on December 4, 2017.\n\n===How They Got Here (2019)===\nOn December 24, 2019 Bravo premiered ''Vanderpump Rules: How They Got Here'', a recap of all 7 previous seasons of ''Vanderpump Rules'' before starting the eighth season on January 7, 2020.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.bravotv.com/vanderpump-rules}}\n* {{IMDb title|2343157}}\n* {{TV Guide|512895}}\n\n{{The Real Housewives}}\n{{Bravo programming}}\n\n[[Category:2013 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Bravo (American TV channel) original programming]]\n[[Category:The Real Housewives spin-offs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Vanderpump Rules\n| image                    = Castofvanderpumprules.jpg\n| genre                    = [[Reality television|Reality]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Lisa Vanderpump]]\n* [[Scheana Shay]]\n* [[Stassi Schroeder]]\n* [[Jax Taylor]]\n* Tom Sandoval\n* [[Kristen Doute]]\n* Katie Maloney-Schwartz\n* Tom Schwartz\n* [[Ariana Madix]]\n* James Kennedy\n* [[Lala Kent]]\n* Brittany Cartwright\n* Beau Clark\n* Dayna Kathan\n* Brett Caprioni\n* Max Boyens\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Dena Deadly\n| opentheme                = \"Raise Your Glass\"\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 8\n| num_episodes             = 146\n| list_episodes            = List of Vanderpump Rules episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Alex Baskin\n* Bill Langworthy\n* Douglas Ross\n* Greg Stewart\n* Ken Todd\n* Lisa Vanderpump\n}}\n| camera                   = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multiple]]\n| runtime                  = 42 minutes\n| company                  = Evolution Media\n| channel                  = [[Bravo (American TV channel)|Bravo]]\n| picture_format           = [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]])<br />[[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2013|1|7}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| related                  = {{Plainlist |\n* ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]''\n* ''[[Vanderpump Rules After Show]]''\n* ''[[Summer House (2017 TV series)|Summer House]]''\n* ''[[Vanderpump Rules: Jax And Brittany Take Kentucky]]''\n}}\n| website                  = http://www.bravotv.com/vanderpump-rules\n}}\n\n'''''Vanderpump Rules''''' is an American [[reality television]] series that premiered on January 7, 2013, on [[Bravo (American TV channel)|Bravo]]. Developed as a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]'', it has aired eight seasons and features [[Lisa Vanderpump]] and the staff at her restaurant SUR in [[West Hollywood, California]]. \n\nThe success of the show has resulted in the spin-off ''[[Vanderpump Rules: Jax And Brittany Take Kentucky]]'', featuring cast members [[Jax Taylor]] and Brittany Cartwright.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/vanderpump-rules-jax-and-brittany-take-kentucky-sneak-peek |title=Jax Taylor Heads to the Farm This Summer for Vanderpump Rules: Jax & Brittany Take Kentucky|date=2017-04-10|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2017-04-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\n''Vanderpump Rules'' follows [[Lisa Vanderpump]]'s employees at SUR, a restaurant in [[West Hollywood]], as they work on building their futures in show business and become entangled in interpersonal drama. The series initially centered around new server [[Scheana Shay|Scheana Marie]] and her relationships with established employees: Stassi, Katie, Kristen, Tom and Jax.\n\n[[Andy Cohen (television personality)|Andy Cohen]] later announced during the February 4, 2013, ''[[Watch What Happens Live with Andy Cohen|Watch What Happens Live]]'' episode that there would be a ''Vanderpump Rules'' reunion. The reunion was filmed on February 9, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Andy Cohen Twitter Status |url=https://twitter.com/BravoAndy/status/300364110992912386|publisher=Twitter |access-date=February 10, 2013}}</ref> It was announced in April 2013 that the series had been renewed for a second season.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bibel|first=Sara|title=Bravo Greenlights 17 New and 18 Returning Unscripted Series |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/04/02/bravo-greenlights-17-new-and-18-returning-unscripted-series/176000/ |publisher=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=April 2, 2013 |access-date=March 11, 2015}}</ref> The second season debut was a two-hour crossover episode with the fourth-season premiere of ''The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills'' on November 4, 2013.<ref name=season2>{{cite press release |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/09/18/bravo-sets-november-premiere-dates-for-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-atlanta-shahs-of-sunset-thicker-than-water-more/203458/ |title=Bravo Sets November Premiere Dates for 'Real Housewives of Beverly Hills & Atlanta', 'Shahs of Sunset', 'Thicker Than Water' & More |last=Bibel|first=Sara|publisher=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=September 18, 2013|accessdate=March 11, 2015}}</ref> The second season reunion was filmed on January 10, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |last=Gajewski|first=Ryan|title=Vanderpump Rules Wraps Taping For Reunion Special&nbsp;\u2014 The Cast Tweets About the Crazy Day |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/vanderpump-rules/articles/2014-01-13-wraps-taping-reunion-special-crazy |publisher=[[Wetpaint]] Entertainment |access-date=January 14, 2014|date=January 13, 2014}}</ref> ''Vanderpump Rules'' was renewed for a third season in April 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/bravo-developing-morgan-spurlock-thom-694382 |title=Bravo Developing Morgan Spurlock, Thom Beers Projects; Orders Real-Time Dating Series |last=Ng|first=Philiana|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=April 8, 2014 |access-date=April 8, 2014}}</ref> The new season premiered on November 3, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thewrap.com/vanderpump-rules-return-set-for-november-stassi-is-back-video/|title=\u2018Vanderpump Rules\u2019 Return Set for November: Stassi Is Back |last=Nededog |first=Jethro |publisher=[[The Wrap]] |date=October 14, 2014 |accessdate=October 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe show was renewed for a fourth season, which premiered on November 2, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/vanderpump-rules-season-4-renewed-bravo-1201535795/ |title=Bravo\u2019s \u2018Vanderpump Rules\u2019 Renewed for Season 4|first=Elizabeth|last=Wagmeister|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|date=July 13, 2015|accessdate=September 17, 2015}}</ref> The show was later renewed for a fifth season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-vanderpump-rules-among-bravo-renewals/ |title=\u2018Real Housewives of Beverly Hills,\u2019 \u2018Vanderpump Rules\u2019 Among Bravo Renewals |accessdate=April 28, 2016|date=April 27, 2016|publisher=[[The Wrap]]|first=Linda|last=Ge}}</ref> On September 26, 2016, the trailer and cast were announced, along with the premiere date of November 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rosenfeld|first1=Laura|title=Vanderpump Rules Returns for Season 5 This November: Here's Your First Look at All the Drama|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/vanderpump-rules-season-5-premiere-date-trailer?cid=soc_dg_fb_PumpRules|website=Bravo|publisher=The Daily Dish|accessdate=September 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bricker|first1=Tierny|title=Vanderpump Rules' Season 5 Teaser Is Here and Has So Many Tears- and Major Wedding Drama|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/797355/vanderpump-rules-season-5-teaser-is-here-and-has-so-many-tears-and-major-wedding-drama|website=E Online|publisher=E News!|accessdate=September 26, 2016}}</ref> On January 9, 2017, the tenth episode of the [[List of Vanderpump Rules episodes#Season 5 (2016\u201317)|fifth season]] of ''Vanderpump Rules'' titled \"Summer House Rules\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Ep 10: Summer House Rules|url=http://www.bravotv.com/vanderpump-rules/season-5/ep-10-the-talk-of-montauk|website=Bravo|accessdate=January 11, 2017|date=January 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bravo Media Celebrates 'Vanderpump Rules' Stars Birthdays in Style with an Epic Two-Hour Special Airing Monday, January 9 at 9PM ET/PT |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2016/12/19/bravo-media-celebrates-vanderpump-rules-stars-birthdays-in-style-with-an-epic-two-hour-special-airing-monday-january-9-at-9pm-et-pt-449311/20161219bravo01/ |website=The Futon Critic|access-date=January 11, 2017|date=December 19, 2016}}</ref> served as a cross-over preview to ''[[Summer House (2017 TV series)|Summer House]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Paiella |first1=Gabriella|title=A Tale of Two Birthday Trips: Part Two |url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2017/01/vanderpump-rules-recap-season-five-ep-ten-summer-house-rules.html |website=New York |department=The Cut|accessdate=January 11, 2017|date=January 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stack|first1=Tim|title='Vanderpump Rules' recap: 'Summer House Rules'|url=http://ew.com/recap/vanderpump-rules-season-5-episode-10/|website=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=January 11, 2017|date=January 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn April 11, 2018 Bravo renewed the show for a seventh season,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/bravo-renews-vanderpump-rules-and-19-other-shows-1202750400/|title=Bravo Renews \u2018Vanderpump Rules\u2019 and 19 Other Shows, Expands to Seven Nights a Week|last=Otterson|first=Joe|date=2018-04-11|work=Variety|access-date=2018-04-12|language=en-US}}</ref> which premiered on December 3, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/vanderpump-rules-season-7-trailer/|title=Engagements and Potential Splits: Relationships are Tested in Vanderpump Rules Season 7 Trailer|author=|date=|website=PEOPLE.com|accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe eighth season premiered on January 7, 2020 with 5 new cast members joining the show.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bravo's \"Vanderpump Rules\" Returns Tuesday, January 7 at 9 PM ET/PT|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/11/07/bravos-vanderpump-rules-returns-tuesday-january-7-at-9-pm-et-pt-328511/20191107bravo01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=November 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Timeline===\n{| style=\"width:60%;\" class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:23%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | Cast Members\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Seasons\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 1\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 2\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 3\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 4\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 5\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 6\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 7\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" | 8\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Lisa Vanderpump]]\n| colspan=\"8\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Scheana Shay]]\n| colspan=\"8\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Stassi Schroeder]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cMain}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"4\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" |[[Jax Taylor]]\n| colspan=\"8\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Tom Sandoval\n| colspan=\"8\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kristen Doute