 | [[Vail Bloom]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Faith Stowers\n| colspan=\"3\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n| {{n/a|}}\n| {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"2\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Raquel Leviss\n| colspan=\"4\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cGuest}}\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Billie Lee\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cRecurring}}\n| {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Charli Burnett\n| colspan=\"7\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Danica Dow\n| colspan=\"7\" {{n/a|}}\n| colspan=\"1\" {{cRecurring}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Lisa Vanderpump]]: A successful restaurateur, the co-owner of SUR. Best known as a former cast member of ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]''.\n* [[Scheana Shay]]: A server at SUR, a singer and aspiring actress.\n* [[Stassi Schroeder]] (Seasons 1-Present, Recurring Season 4): A former server at SUR. \n* [[Jax Taylor]]: A bartender at SUR.\n* Tom Sandoval: A former bartender at SUR, now Lisa's business partner at TomTom.\n* [[Kristen Doute]]: A former server at SUR, now a clothing designer\n* Katie Maloney-Schwartz: A former server at SUR, married to Tom Schwartz.\n* Tom Schwartz: (Season 3-Present, Recurring Seasons 1-2) Katie's husband, now Lisa's business partner at TomTom.\n*[[Ariana Madix]]: (Season 3-Present, Recurring Season 2) A former bartender at SUR, in a relationship with Tom Sandoval.\n* James Kennedy: (Season 4-Present, Recurring Season 3) A former busboy at SUR, now a DJ.\n* Lala Kent: (Season 6-Present, Recurring Seasons 4-5) A former hostess at SUR, now engaged to Hollywood producer [[Randall Emmett]].\n* Brittany Cartwright: (Season 6-Present, Recurring Season 5) Jax's wife, a former server at SUR.\n* Beau Clark: (Season 8-present, Recurring Season 7) Stassi's fianc\u00e9.\n* Dayna Kathan: (Season 8-present) A hostess and server at TomTom and SUR.\n* Max Boyens: (Season 8-present) The general manager at TomTom.\n* Brett Caprioni: (Season 8-present) A server at SUR.\n\n===Recurring cast===\n* Ken Todd: Lisa Vanderpump's husband, the co-owner of SUR and successful restaurateur\n*Peter Madrigal: The manager of SUR.\n* Mike Shay: (Season 1-5) Scheana's ex-husband.\n*Tina McDowelle: (Season 1-3) A former server at SUR, a singer.\n*Frank Herlihy: (Season 1) A former bartender at SUR\n*[[Laura-Leigh]]: (Season 1) A former server at SUR, an actress known for [[The Ward (film)|''The Ward'']] and [[The Client List (TV series)|''The Client List'']]\n* Kristina Kelly: (Season 2-7) Stassi's friend, a server at SUR.\n*[[Vail Bloom]]: (Season 3) A former hostess at SUR, an [[Daytime Emmy Award|Emmy]]-nominated actress known for ''[[The Young and the Restless]]''.\n* Faith Stowers: (Seasons 4, 6) A former server at SUR. \n* Raquel Leviss: (Season 5-present) James's girlfriend, a server at SUR.<ref>http://www.bravotv.com/vanderpump-rules/season-5/blogs/5-things-you-need-to-know-about-james-kennedys-girlfriend-raquel</ref>\n* Billie Lee: (Season 6-7) A former hostess at SUR.\n* Charli Burnett: (Season 8-present) A server at SUR.\n* Danica Dow: (Season 8-present) An assistant manager at SUR.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of Vanderpump Rules episodes}}\n{{:List of Vanderpump Rules episodes}}\n\n===After Show (2015-16)===\nOn November 6, 2015, Bravo premiered a [[talk show]] titled ''[[Vanderpump Rules After Show]]'' which features conversations between the cast members of ''Vanderpump Rules'' discussing the same week's events and answering questions about their lives both on and off the show. The talk show was hosted by [[Julie Goldman]] and Brandy Howard.\n\n===How They Got Here (2017)===\nOn November 27, 2017 Bravo premiered ''[[Vanderpump Rules: How They Got Here]]'', a recap of all five previous seasons of ''Vanderpump Rules'' before starting the sixth season on December 4, 2017.\n\n===How They Got Here (2019)===\nOn December 24, 2019 Bravo premiered ''Vanderpump Rules: How They Got Here'', a recap of all 7 previous seasons of ''Vanderpump Rules'' before starting the eighth season on January 7, 2020.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.bravotv.com/vanderpump-rules}}\n* {{IMDb title|2343157}}\n* {{TV Guide|512895}}\n\n{{The Real Housewives}}\n{{Bravo programming}}\n\n[[Category:2013 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Bravo (American TV channel) original programming]]\n[[Category:The Real Housewives spin-offs]]\n", "name_user": "Proserpine", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRecurring cast", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanderpump_Rules"}
{"title_page": "Kaleshwaram", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=June 2013}}\n{{original research|date=September 2012}}\n{{more footnotes|date=September 2012}}\n}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Kaleshwaram\n| other_name                      = Kaleswaram\n| settlement_type                 = \n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = Kaleshwara Muktheswara Swamy Temple\n| image_map                       = \n| map_alt                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Telangana#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = \u2190\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|18|48|41|N|79|54|24|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = India\n| subdivision_type1               = State\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Telangana]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Jayashankar Bhupalpally district|Bhupalpally]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| government_type                 = Village Panchayat\n| blank1_name_sec2                = [[Climatic]]\n| blank1_info_sec2                = [[Climatic regions of India|Tropical]] <small>([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]])</small>\n| blank2_name_sec2                = [[Precipitation (meteorology)|Precipitation]]\n| blank2_info_sec2                = {{convert|995|mm|in}}\n| blank3_name_sec2                = Avg. annual temperature\n| blank3_info_sec2                = {{convert|31|\u00b0C|\u00b0F}}\n| blank4_name_sec2                = Avg. summer temperature\n| blank4_info_sec2                = {{convert|44|\u00b0C|\u00b0F}}\n| blank5_name_sec2                = Avg. winter temperature\n| blank5_info_sec2                = {{convert|20|\u00b0C|\u00b0F}}\n| website                         = [https://www.kaleshwaramproject.com]\n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n\n'''Kaleshwaram''' is a village in [[Mahadevpur]] [[Mandal]] in [[Jayashankar Bhupalpally district|Bhoopalpally district]] in the [[Indian state]] of [[Telangana]]. This name refers more broadly to the state of [[Telangana]] & Kaleshwaram Temple.\n\nKaleshwaram is at the juncture of the rivers Godavari and its Pranahita tributary. It is 277 kilometres from [[Hyderabad]], 125 kilometres from [[Karimnagar]], 115 kilometres from [[Warangal]], 95 kilometres from [[Ramagundam railway station]], 90 kilometres from [[Godavarikhani]], 75 kilometres from [[Parkal]] and 60 kilometres from [[Manthani]]. This place is also popularly known as second kashi or southern Indian kashi. It is 16.5 kilometres from Sironcha, Maharashtra.\n\n==Legend==\nLegend claims that a long time ago, a Vaishya had performed an ''Abhisheka'' to Lord Kaleshwara Mukteswara with hundreds of milk pots, and the milk evolved at the ''sangamam'' of Godavari and Pranahita.is help of muntha surya vamshi yadav only we can did it\n\n==Transport==\nTsrtc Bus services are available from [[Hyderabad]], [[Godavarikhani]], [[Warangal]], [[Parkal]], [[Karimnagar]], [[Manthani]], and [[Peddapalli, Peddapalli district|Peddapalli]].\nMainly [[Godavarikhani]], [[Bhupalpalle|Bhopalpally]], [[Manthani]] bus depot runs buses to many cities and towns\n\n==Temple==\n{{main|Kaleshwara Mukteswara Swamy Temple}}\n[[File:Kaleswaram.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Kaleshwara Mukteswara Swamy Temple]], Mahadevpur Mandal]]\nIt is the site of a temple of the [[Hindu]] god [[Shiva]]. The temple is significant because of the two Shiva Lingas that are found on a single pedestal. These Linga are named Lord Shiva and Lord [[Yama]]. Collectively, they known as Kaleshwara Mukteswara Swamy. Kaleshwaram is one of three Shiva temples mentioned in Trilinga Desham, or \"Land of Three Lingas.\"\n\nThe holy place draws tourists during the [[Kartika (month)|Karthika]] Month of the Indian Calendar, 16 November \u2013 15 December. Holy baths are held during 6\u201317 of December. People who bathe here first visit [[Lord Ganesha]], then pray to Lord Yama and then to Lord Shiva.\n[[File:Vasavi Temple.jpg|thumb|176x176px]]\nIn Year 2018 March a new temple Sri Vasavi Kanyaka Parameswari temple opened within 2 mintues wasl from Kaleshwara Mukteswara Swamy Temple. Adjacent to it we have a new Nitya Anna Dhana Vysya Satram too. Temple is funded and built by Rajaiah and Satyavathi Devi Daram. Everyday daily rituals are being performed by priest.\n\n==Kaleshwaram Lift Irrigation Project==\n\nThe [[Kaleshwaram Lift Irrigation Project]] is a major irrigation project that was started in 2016. The massive project is intended to meet the irrigation needs of nearly three-fourths of Telangana with its headworks taken up at a cost of \u20b980,500 crore.<ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/kaleshwaram-to-make-a-date-with-history-today/article28089693.ece</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://kaleshwaramtemple.in Visit www.KaleshwaramTemple.in \u2013 Kaleshwaram Devasthanam \u2013 Sri Kaleshwara Muktheeshwara Devasthanam ]\n*[https://traveltimings.in/hyderabad-kaleshwaram/ Visit https://traveltimings.in/hyderabad-kaleshwaram/ \u2013 For Hyderabad to Kaleshwaram Bus Timings \u2013 For Sri Kaleshwara Muktheeshwara Devasthanam ]\n*[https://www.kaleshwaramproject.com The Kaleshwaram Lift Irrigation Project website]\n\n{{Trilinga Kshetras}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Karimnagar district]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{More citations needed|date=June 2013}}\n{{original research|date=September 2012}}\n{{more footnotes|date=September 20